

'''Important notice''': Franco Iacomella was active in the P2P Foundation and associated groups like the Commons Strategies Group, but was discovered to be actively manipulating, through filtering/blockings/deletions the communications of the different groups he was active in.

A public letter listing his activities, the parties affected, and the proofs was published by both the P2P Foundation and the [[Commons Strategies Group]]

See for example:

* from P2P-F, [[Statement of Separation with Franco Iacomella]]
* from the CSG, [http://blog.p2pfoundation.net/a-message-of-the-commons-strategies-group-on-a-recent-case-of-communications-manipulation/2013/09/07 A message of the Commons Strategies Group on a recent case of communications manipulation]



Michel Bauwens, P2P Foundation, Luneburg July 31, 2013

